{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:psalms.105",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 105,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 105 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:1",
      "text": "Alleluia. - Give thanks to the Lord, and call upon his name; declare his works among the heathen.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:2",
      "text": "Sing to him, yea, sing praises to him: tell forth all his wonderful works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:3",
      "text": "Glory in his holy name: let the heart of them that seek the Lord rejoice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:4",
      "text": "Seek ye the Lord, and be strengthened; seek his face continually.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:5",
      "text": "Remember his wonderful works that he has done; his wonders, and the judgements of his mouth;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:6",
      "text": "ye seed of Abraam, his servants, ye children of Jacob, his chosen ones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:7",
      "text": "He is the Lord our God; his judgements are in all the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:8",
      "text": "He has remembered his covenant for ever, the word which he commanded for a thousand generation:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:9",
      "text": "which he established as a covenant to Abraam, and he remembered his oath to Isaac.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:10",
      "text": "And he established it to Jacob for an ordinance, and to Israel for an everlasting covenant;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:11",
      "text": "saying To thee will I give the land of Chanaan, the line of your inheritance:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:12",
      "text": "when they were few in number, very few, and sojourners in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:13",
      "text": "And they went from nation to nation, and from one kingdom to another people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:14",
      "text": "He suffered no man to wrong them; and he rebuked kings for their sakes:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:15",
      "text": "saying, Touch not my anointed ones; and do my prophets no harm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:16",
      "text": "Moreover he called for a famine upon the land; he broke the whole support of bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:17",
      "text": "He sent a man before them; Joseph was sold for a slave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:18",
      "text": "They hurt his feet with fetters; his soul passed into iron,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:19",
      "text": "until the time that his cause came on; the word of the Lord tried him as fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:20",
      "text": "The king sent and loosed him; even the prince of the people, and let him go free.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.21",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:21",
      "text": "He made him Lord over his house, and ruler of all his substance;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.22",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:22",
      "text": "to chastise his rulers at his pleasure, and to teach his elders wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.23",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:23",
      "text": "Israel also came into Egypt, and Jacob sojourned in the land of Cham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.24",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:24",
      "text": "And he increased his people greatly, and made them stronger than their enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.25",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:25",
      "text": "And he turned their heart to hate his people, to deal craftily with his servants.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.26",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:26",
      "text": "He sent forth Moses his servant, and Aaron whom he had chosen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.27",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:27",
      "text": "He established among them his signs, and his wonders in the land of Cham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.28",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:28",
      "text": "He sent forth darkness, and made it dark; yet they rebelled against his words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.29",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:29",
      "text": "He turned their waters into blood, and slew their fish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.30",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:30",
      "text": "Their land produced frogs abundantly, in the chambers of their kings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.31",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:31",
      "text": "He spoke, and the dog-fly came, and lice in all their coasts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.32",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:32",
      "text": "He turned their rain into hail, and sent flaming fire in their land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.33",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:33",
      "text": "And he smote their vines and their fig trees; and broke every tree of their coast.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.34",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:34",
      "text": "He spoke, and the locust came, and caterpillars innumerable,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.35",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:35",
      "text": "and devoured all the grass in their land, and devoured the fruit of the ground.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.36",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:36",
      "text": "He smote also every first-born of their land, the first-fruits of all their labour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.37",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:37",
      "text": "And he brought them out with silver and gold; and there was not a feeble one among their tribes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.38",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:38",
      "text": "Egypt rejoiced at their departing; for the fear of them fell upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.39",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:39",
      "text": "He spread out a cloud for a covering to them, and fire to give them light by night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.40",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:40",
      "text": "They asked, and the quail came, and he satisfied them with the bread of heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.41",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:41",
      "text": "He clave the rock, and the waters flowed, rivers ran in dry places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.42",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:42",
      "text": "For he remembered his holy word, which he promised to Abraam his servant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.43",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:43",
      "text": "And he brought out his people with exultation, and his chosen with joy;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.44",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:44",
      "text": "and gave them the lands of the heathen; and they inherited the labours of the people;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.105.45",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:45",
      "text": "that they might keep his ordinances, and diligently seek his law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
